(secondQuint)Safety of Vitamin D Supplementation in Older Persons.

 120 ambulatory men and women ages 65 to 95 will be enrolled in this study.

 Each subject will participate in the clinical trial for 6 months.

 Parathyroid hormone, vitamin D, and serum and urinary calcium will be measured periodically.

 Physical performance will be tested at baseline and throughout the study.

